# Jekyll Blog Project Directory Structure Rules

## Core Jekyll Directories

### `_posts/` - Blog Posts
- **Purpose**: Directory for storing all blog posts
- **File naming convention**: `YYYY-MM-DD-title.markdown` format
- **Content**: Technical blog posts (Java, JavaScript, NestJS, Swift, Android, iOS, DB, Electron, GraphQL, etc.)
- **Examples**: `2024-03-02-HDC-EP-analyze.markdown`, `2023-07-30-nestjs-install.markdown`

### `_layouts/` - Page Layouts
- **Purpose**: Jekyll page layout templates
- **Files**:
  - `default.html`: Default layout
  - `post.html`: Blog post layout
  - `page.html`: General page layout
  - `about_page.html`: About page layout
  - `archive.html`: Archive page layout

### `_includes/` - Reusable Components
- **Purpose**: HTML components reused across multiple pages
- **Files**:
  - `header.html`: Site header
  - `footer.html`: Site footer
  - `head.html`: HTML head section
  - `advertisement.html`, `advertisementitem.html`: Advertisement-related components
  - `page_divider.html`: Page divider

### `_sass/` - SCSS Stylesheets
- **Purpose**: SCSS files for site styling
- **Structure**:
  - `_layout.scss`: Main layout styles
  - `base/`: Base styles (buttons, forms, grid, typography, etc.)
  - `bourbon/`: Bourbon CSS framework
  - `neat/`: Neat grid system

## Static File Directories

### `assets/` - Static Assets
- **Purpose**: Images, icons, and other static files
- **Structure**:
  - `icons/`: Favicons and app icons (Android, Apple, MS)
  - `Posts/`: Blog post related images
  - `Bluemix/`, `Electron/`, `javascript_tdd_image/`: Technology-specific images
  - `header_image.jpg`, `icon.png`, `logo.png`: Site main images

### `css/` - Compiled CSS
- **Purpose**: CSS files compiled from SCSS
- **File**: `main.scss` (automatically compiled to CSS by Jekyll)

### `js/` - JavaScript Files
- **Purpose**: Client-side JavaScript files

## Configuration and Meta Files

### Root Level Files
- `_config.yml`: Jekyll site configuration (title, URL, plugins, categories, etc.)
- `Gemfile`, `Gemfile.lock`: Ruby dependency management
- `index.html`: Homepage
- `about.md`: About page
- `posts.html`: Post listing page

### SEO and Feed Files
- `feed.xml`: RSS feed
- `naverfeed.xml`: Naver feed
- `robots.txt`: Search engine crawling rules
- `ads.txt`: Advertisement-related settings

### CI/CD and License
- `circle.yml`: CircleCI configuration
- `LICENSE.md`: License information
- `README.md`: Project description

## File Creation Rules

1. **New Posts**: Create in `_posts/` directory with `YYYY-MM-DD-title.markdown` format
2. **New Layouts**: Create in `_layouts/` directory with `.html` extension
3. **New Components**: Create in `_includes/` directory with `.html` extension
4. **New Styles**: Create in `_sass/` directory with `_` prefix and `.scss` extension
5. **New Images**: Store in appropriate subfolder under `assets/` directory
6. **New Pages**: Create at root level with `.html` or `.md` extension

## Important Notes

- Jekyll special directories (`_posts`, `_layouts`, `_includes`, `_sass`) start with underscore
- Use lowercase and hyphens for all file names
- Organize image files by category under `assets/` directory
- Make configuration changes only in `_config.yml`